    "body": "Hi @olehmisar, you can do that with the `HARDHAT_TYPECHECK` environment variable. So, doing `export HARDHAT_TYPECHECK=true` should enable typechecking for all successive commands in that shell session. Adding that command to your shell configuration would enable typechecking by default (but it wouldn't be shared with the rest of your team).\r\n\r\nWe can't have an option for this in the configuration itself because by the time the config is read ts-node will be already loaded.",
